text.section:
"Home health care" includes any of the following services:
Audiology and speech pathology;
Dietary and nutritional services;
Drug services;
Home health aid;
Laboratory;
Medical social services;
Nursing;
Occupational therapy;
Physical therapy;
Provision of invasive medical equipment; and
Home medical equipment services.

"Medical equipment" means technologically sophisticated medical devices including:
Oxygen and oxygen delivery systems;
Ventilators;
Respiratory disease management devices;
Electronic and computer driven wheelchairs and seating systems;
Apnea monitors;
Transcutaneous electrical nerve stimulator (T.E.N.S.) units;
Low air loss cutaneous pressure management devices;
Sequential compression devices;
Neonatal home phototherapy devices;
Feeding pumps; and
Other similar equipment as defined in regulations established by the Secretary.

section.section:
"Residential service agency" does not include:
A home health agency that is licensed under the provisions of Subtitle 4 of this title;
A person required to be licensed as a home health agency under the provisions of Subtitle 4 of this title;
A home-based hospice care program that is licensed under the provisions of Subtitle 9 of this title;
A hospital that is licensed under the provisions of Subtitle 3 of this title;
A related institution that is licensed under the provisions of Subtitle 3 of this title;
Personal care providers under the Medical Assistance Personal Care Program;
Any person practicing a health occupation that the person is authorized to practice under the Health Occupations Article;
A nursing referral service agency that is licensed under Subtitle 4B of this title;
A group of persons licensed under the same title of the Health Occupations Article practicing as a business; or
Residential rehabilitation services providers approved under regulations adopted by the State Mental Health Authority.
